.TH HELLO_GFORTRAN_O2 1 "" "" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hello_gfortran_O2 \- recovered gfortran -O2 hello-style program
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hello_gfortran_O2
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hello_gfortran_O2
is a program recovered from a binary originally compiled from Fortran source
using
.B gfortran
at optimization level
.BR -O2 .
The recovered sources are presented in C: a small
.B main.c
entry point that bootstraps the Fortran runtime and invokes the original
Fortran main program, together with
.B src/core.c
which holds the remaining recovered functions that were not clustered into a
more specific module.
.PP
The program is intended as a reference for inspecting the shape of a
.B gfortran
.B -O2
build after recovery, and as a starting point for further analysis.
.SH OPTIONS
.B hello_gfortran_O2
does not document any specific options. Any arguments supplied on the command
line are passed through to the recovered program as-is.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR gfortran (1),
.BR cmake (1),
.BR cc (1)
